  pages={1-7},
  abstract={Multi-step solar irradiance forecast is an important part of a successful power grid management. However that forecast can be difficult due to nonlinear patterns and random fluctuation. This work applies statistical and machine learning methods to forecast solar irradiance time series from three different locations of Brazil. The applied models are: Autoregressive Integrated Moving Average (ARIMA), Deep Belief Network (DBN), Extreme Learning Machine (ELM), Multi Layer Perceptron neural network (MLP), Random Forest (RF), and Support Vector Regression (SVR). Taking into account these methods, an ensemble of them is proposed, which has the objective of reducing: the uncertainty of selecting a single model, overfitting, and underfitting. Compared with single models and based on two performance metrics, the ensemble found good overall results when applied in the time series with horizons of 6, 12 and 24 hours ahead.},
